Introduction to a specific research question of Finno-Ugic etymology, lexikology, and morphosyntax: origin of languages and areal distribution, the research tradition behind this question, the researchability of it on the base of existing materials. Students write a supervised paper on language change.Objectives/eesmärkid:  Strenghtening the diachronic component in the Curriculum of Estonian and Finnougric-Studies.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The students acquire knowledge about differents historical aspects of the Finno-Ugric language family as well as the skill of critically evaluating connections between historical and contemporary developments.
